    "content": "A person stands at point A and needs to reach point D by the shortest path possible. Points A and D are on opposite ends of a rectangular area, with point O as a reference point inside the rectangle. The distance AO is equal to BC, and both are 3 km. The distance from point C to point D is 10 km, and from point B to A (BA) is 6 km. What is the shortest distance from point A to point D?",
    "options": [
